http://allafrica.com/stories/201505010654.html?viewall=1

Fri 1 May 2015 Netherlands: Possible Ebola patient examined in Nijmegen
http://www.nltimes.nl/2015/05/01/possible-ebola-patient-examined-in-nijmegen/
[The patient was originally admitted to the Rijnstate Hospital in Arnhem on Thu 30 Apr 2015. After an examination, the doctors decided to transfer the patient to an academic hospital, Radboud University Medical Center in Nijmegen, where patient was admitted to isolation.]

Fri 1 May 2015 Nigeria: Govt, U.S. military commence Ebola vaccine tests
http://allafrica.com/stories/201505010432.html?viewall=1

Tue 28 Apr 2015 Sierra Leone Post-Ebola: Leadership needed to keep pregnant young girls in school
http://www.huffingtonpost.com/kolleen-bouchane/post-ebola-sierra-leone-l_b_7161208.html

Thu 30 Apr 2015 Sierra Leone: Singapore sends Public Health Officer to participate in WHO Ebola efforts
http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singapore-sends-public/1816200.html
[The Public Health Officer will join the WPRO Ebola Support Team (which was launched in January 2015, based in Port Loko, Sierra Leone) and will provide Sierra Leone with technical and administrative support in ongoing Ebola efforts.]

Thu 30 Apr 2015 Zambia: Copperbelt prepares preventative measures against Ebola
http://allafrica.com/stories/201504300512.html?viewall=1
[Zambia's Parliamentary Committee on Health has been assured that the Copperbelt Provincial medical team has put in place measures that will help minimize the risks of an outbreak of the Ebola virus. This is a prudent precaution because it now seems possible that Ebola virus is widely distributed, undetected, in wildlife in forested areas of Africa. - Mod.JW]

29 Apr 2015 UK: Ebola scare at Jersey Hospital
http://jerseyeveningpost.com/news/2015/04/29/ebola-scare-at-jersey-hospital/
[Emergency procedures were initiated after a patient who had traveled from Sierra Leone to the British Channel island of Jersey arrived at the hospital with a fever on the evening of 27 Apr 2015. Isolation measures were undertaken, and health-care workers used personal protective equipment while working with the patient. Subsequently, Ebola testing ruled out the disease. Patient is still hospitalized in a critical, but stable condition.]

Fri 1 May 2015 UK: Ebola virus disease outbreak in West Africa (December 2013 to present)
https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/425412/EVD_Epidemiological_Update_1_May_v1.pdf

Tue 28 Apr 2015 USA (North Carolina): Ebola tests are negative for Carolinas Medical Center patient
http://www.charlotteobserver.com/news/local/article19808697.html
[The patient had been in one of the West African Ebola-outbreak countries, and had been treated in an outpatient setting before admission to CMC. According to a statement from the hospital, the likelihood of the patient having Ebola virus disease is very low. The patient, who had been placed in isolation prior to the results of testing were known, will be moved into a regular hospital room to continue treatment.]

Sat 2 May 2015 USA (Texas): Patient in Texas tests negative for Ebola
http://abcnewsradioonline.com/health-news/patient-in-texas-tests-negative-for-ebola.html

